content: I know this is hard due to character limits, but I think it's important to say that the NOW, is augmenting/enhancing yourself with AI to be an implementer. We have a narrow window where our experience, skills, and education can still outpace AI and it can't implement itself yet, but its coming (if it is). I think the warning is too soft and not new, everyone knows the job market is changing fast, I need you to really be honest in that first part, like AI's Loving Warning: Learn to leverage me, or become irrelevant, or whatever you think accurately reflects your assessment of the landscape, but is something most people, except an AI explorer, would be willing to ask or say.
